Product Description


Meta Fundamentals

A great value for groups, Meta Fundamentals styles combine function with the utmost in labcoat value.

  • Great for groups
  • Style and function
  • Soil Release

Meta Fundamentals 15113 Women's 37" Labcoat

GREAT COATS FOR GROUPS

This labcoat features a five-button closure, two lower patch pockets, one chest pocket, hand access slits and one-piece back and sleeve.

  • 65% Polyester, 35% Cotton Poplin with Soil Release
  • Five-button front closure
  • Two lower patch pockets
  • One chest pocket
  • One-piece back and sleeve
  • Hand access slits
  • Sizes: XXS-5X, XST-2XT

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    5.0 out of 5 stars glad to find this on Amazon
    Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2014
    Verified Purchase
    I run through white coats, about 2-4 a year. They just become off-white, especially around the sleeves. I happen to like this brand and have bought elsewhere before, so I know my size.
    This is not the thickest white coat, but I practice in Houston, and I don't really want a heavy white coat. I also don't like the coats with a button or knotted button in the back because when I lean on it, the button bothers me.
    This is a simple coat, 5 front buttons, two large front pockets and a smaller breast pocket, and two side slits to access your pant pockets.

  • ann_chovy
    4.0 out of 5 stars 4.5/5 Good lab coat
    Reviewed in the United States on February 19, 2013
    Verified Purchase
    I bought this lab coat for anatomy lab.

    While I am usually a Small in clothing, I ordered an Extra Small for this lab coat. It fits a bit snug in the shoulders (I do have broad shoulders though, so keep that in mind), but it doesn't hinder my movement at all. If I sized down any smaller, I think I'd have a problem with any upper body movement. The coat length comes to about my knee, but that is to be expected (I'm under 5'0").

    The material is a bit thin & stiff, but it seems sturdy and well made for its purpose.
